  "body": "**Is this a BUG REPORT or FEATURE REQUEST?** (choose one): Bug Report\r\n\r\n**Kubernetes version** (use `kubectl version`): N/A\r\n\r\n\r\n**Environment**: \r\n- **Cloud provider or hardware configuration**: ALL\r\n- **OS** (e.g. from /etc/os-release): Ubuntu 16.04\r\n- **Kernel** (e.g. `uname -a`): N/A\r\n- **Install tools**: Juju\r\n\r\n\r\n**What happened**:  During the initialization of the kubernetes-master charm and addons snap package is installed. This sets the state `cdk-addons.available` which enables a polling loop on every hook execution with a 3 minute timeout wait that blocks further execution of the events on every cycle, about 2 relations too soon thus bloating the installation time by up to an additional 10 minutes.\r\n\r\n\r\n**What you expected to happen**:\r\nThe method to be properly guarded and not block before a worker node has joined the cluster to provide a workspace for those containers to launch.\r\n\r\n**How to reproduce it** (as minimally and precisely as possible):\r\nDeploy any recent Canonical Kubernetes bundle and watch the cycle timer on the `idle_status` method.\r\n\r\n**Anything else we need to know**:\r\n\r\n",
